This is a package for using [[CDB]] (constant database) with [[Postfix]].

I use this package and user information storage system because [[CDB]] is super fast and easy to manage with postmap. I use it primarily on [[SMTP]] gateways to store whether or not an email address exists on the networks I manage - i.e. the relay_recipient_maps [[Postfix]] configuration option.

The raw file looks like this:

<pre class="sh_sh">
user@example.com OK
</pre>

Then I compile it with postmap:

<pre class="sh_sh">
postmap cdb:/etc/postfix/file
</pre>

And the [[Postfix]] configuration option:

<pre class="sh_sh">
relay_recipient_maps = cdb:/etc/postfix/file
</pre>

